<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="471" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1747,2005]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1747,1772]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Salgado &amp; Ruiz, 2019" authorityName="Salgado &amp; Ruiz" authorityYear="2019" box="[328,460,1747,1771]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shenlong" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[328,460,1747,1771]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">A. shenlong</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[468,558,1747,1772]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[468,558,1747,1772]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Salgado &amp; Ruiz, 2017" authorityName="Salgado &amp; Ruiz" authorityYear="2017" box="[705,1181,1747,1772]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="draconicaudatus">
<emphasis box="[705,924,1747,1771]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">A. draconicaudatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Salgado, A. &amp; Ruiz, G. R." box="[932,1181,1747,1772]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" pagination="401 - 437" refId="ref8937" refString="Salgado, A. &amp; Ruiz, G. R. S (2017) Ten new species of Amphidraus Simon, 1900 (Araneae: Salticidae: Euophryini) and three new combinations. Zootaxa, 4312 (3), 401 - 437. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4312.3.1" type="journal article" year="2017">Salgado &amp; Ruiz, 2017</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by having an elongate and stout projection on the retrolateral border of the embolic disc that extends towards the retrolateral tegulum border and bears several branches (
<figureCitation box="[563,650,1813,1838]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1923,1945]" captionTargetBox="[159,1422,795,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[159,1423,795,1903]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 21. Amphidraus shenlong sp. nov. A–B male (A dorsal, B ventral); C–F left male palp (C ventral; D retroventral; E bulb, ventral; F femur + patella + tibia, retrolateral). Abbreviations: cc, cymbial conductor; dPED, distal process on embolic disc; e, embolus shaft; ef, embolic filament; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apophysis; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc. White arrow in D shows branchy projection of embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601388/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Figs 21</figureCitation>
C–D, 26A, 27A), and by having the RvTA ventrally projected with projections on its border (
<figureCitation box="[442,543,1847,1872]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1923,1945]" captionTargetBox="[159,1422,795,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[159,1423,795,1903]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 21. Amphidraus shenlong sp. nov. A–B male (A dorsal, B ventral); C–F left male palp (C ventral; D retroventral; E bulb, ventral; F femur + patella + tibia, retrolateral). Abbreviations: cc, cymbial conductor; dPED, distal process on embolic disc; e, embolus shaft; ef, embolic filament; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apophysis; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc. White arrow in D shows branchy projection of embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601388/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Figs 21F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[555,605,1847,1871]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1670,1692]" captionTargetBox="[177,1383,890,1615]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[151,1436,879,1648]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 22. Amphidraus shenlong sp. nov., left male palp (A ventral; B retrolateral). Abbreviations: cc, cymbial conductor; dPED, distal processes on embolic disc; e, embolus shaft; ed, embolic disc; ef, embolic filament; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apophysis; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601390/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">22B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[617,669,1847,1872]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1594,1616]" captionTargetBox="[170,1396,218,1541]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,203,1563]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 26. Left male palp in Amphidraus spp. A–D, G Amphidraus draconicaudatus Salgado &amp; Ruiz, 2017. A–B, G new specimen from Pium (A bulb, ventral; B retroventral; G tibia, retrolateral). C–D specimen from Caseara (C bulb, ventral; D retroventral). E–F, H Amphidraus shenlong sp. nov. (E bulb, ventral; F retroventral; H tibia, retrolateral). Abbreviations: dPED, distal process on embolic disc; e, embolus shaft; ef, embolic filament; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apophysis; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601398/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">26G</figureCitation>
). However, 
<taxonomicName authority="Salgado &amp; Ruiz, 2019" authorityName="Salgado &amp; Ruiz" authorityYear="2019" box="[805,938,1847,1871]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shenlong" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[805,938,1847,1871]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">A. shenlong</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[946,1036,1847,1872]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[946,1036,1847,1872]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be distinguished by having the RvTA with four projections (three with acute tip and one with serrated tip) and the RTA serrated tip reaching the same height of the RvTA tip along palp axis (
<figureCitation box="[662,763,1913,1938]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1923,1945]" captionTargetBox="[159,1422,795,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[159,1423,795,1903]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 21. Amphidraus shenlong sp. nov. A–B male (A dorsal, B ventral); C–F left male palp (C ventral; D retroventral; E bulb, ventral; F femur + patella + tibia, retrolateral). Abbreviations: cc, cymbial conductor; dPED, distal process on embolic disc; e, embolus shaft; ef, embolic filament; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apophysis; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc. White arrow in D shows branchy projection of embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601388/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Figs 21F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[775,824,1914,1938]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1670,1692]" captionTargetBox="[177,1383,890,1615]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[151,1436,879,1648]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 22. Amphidraus shenlong sp. nov., left male palp (A ventral; B retrolateral). Abbreviations: cc, cymbial conductor; dPED, distal processes on embolic disc; e, embolus shaft; ed, embolic disc; ef, embolic filament; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apophysis; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601390/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">22B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[836,888,1913,1938]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1594,1616]" captionTargetBox="[170,1396,218,1541]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,203,1563]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 26. Left male palp in Amphidraus spp. A–D, G Amphidraus draconicaudatus Salgado &amp; Ruiz, 2017. A–B, G new specimen from Pium (A bulb, ventral; B retroventral; G tibia, retrolateral). C–D specimen from Caseara (C bulb, ventral; D retroventral). E–F, H Amphidraus shenlong sp. nov. (E bulb, ventral; F retroventral; H tibia, retrolateral). Abbreviations: dPED, distal process on embolic disc; e, embolus shaft; ef, embolic filament; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apophysis; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601398/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">26H</figureCitation>
), whereas in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salgado &amp; Ruiz" authorityYear="2017" box="[1036,1255,1914,1938]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="draconicaudatus">
<emphasis box="[1036,1255,1914,1938]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">A. draconicaudatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the RvTA has a single serrated projection and the RTA is reduced to spikes (
<figureCitation box="[824,928,1947,1972]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1594,1616]" captionTargetBox="[170,1396,218,1541]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,203,1563]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 26. Left male palp in Amphidraus spp. A–D, G Amphidraus draconicaudatus Salgado &amp; Ruiz, 2017. A–B, G new specimen from Pium (A bulb, ventral; B retroventral; G tibia, retrolateral). C–D specimen from Caseara (C bulb, ventral; D retroventral). E–F, H Amphidraus shenlong sp. nov. (E bulb, ventral; F retroventral; H tibia, retrolateral). Abbreviations: dPED, distal process on embolic disc; e, embolus shaft; ef, embolic filament; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apophysis; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601398/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Figs 26G</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[939,968,1947,1971]" captionStart="FIGURE 27" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1131,1153]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,228,1080]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[151,1436,228,1080]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 27. Copulatory structures of Amphidraus draconicaudatus Salgado &amp; Ruiz, 2017. A–D left male palp (A embolic disc, ventral; patella + tibia, retrolateral; C detail of RvTA projection; D detail of reduced RTA). E epigyne/vulva, dorsal. Abbreviations: dPED, distal processes on embolic disc; e, embolus shaft; ef, embolic filament; po, coupling pocket; RvTA, retroventral tibial apophysis; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc. White arrows in B and C show projection on RvTA, and black arrow in C shows one spike of the reduced RTA." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601400/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">27</figureCitation>
C–D).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="472" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1747,2005]" lastBlockId="21.[151,1437,151,576]" lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="472" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,725,1980,2005]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">
Description. Male 
<typeStatus box="[424,527,1980,2005]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">holotype</typeStatus>
(MPEG 35020).
</emphasis>
Total length: 2.68. Carapace 1.31 long, 0.89 wide, 0.69 high. Ocular quadrangle 0.71 long. Anterior eye row 1.01 wide, posterior 0.86 wide. Legs 3412. Length of legs: I 1.82 (0.61 + 0.62 + 0.59); II 1.68 (0.59 + 0.57 + 0.52); III 2.42 (0.83 + 0.84 + 0.75); IV 2.29 (0.69 + 0.75 + 0.85). Chelicera with pocket on outer surface (between dorsum and retrolateral face) (
<figureCitation box="[1041,1145,218,243]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1966,1988]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1345,1922]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[151,1436,1345,1922]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 28. Right chelicera, retrolateral (A Amphidraus draconicaudatus, B A. shenlong sp. nov. C A. draconitupan sp. nov.). Black arrow shows pocket on outer face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601402/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Fig. 28B</figureCitation>
). Palp (
<figureCitation box="[1229,1312,218,243]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1923,1945]" captionTargetBox="[159,1422,795,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[159,1423,795,1903]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 21. Amphidraus shenlong sp. nov. A–B male (A dorsal, B ventral); C–F left male palp (C ventral; D retroventral; E bulb, ventral; F femur + patella + tibia, retrolateral). Abbreviations: cc, cymbial conductor; dPED, distal process on embolic disc; e, embolus shaft; ef, embolic filament; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apophysis; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc. White arrow in D shows branchy projection of embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601388/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Figs 21</figureCitation>
C–F, 22A– B): femur with median-ventral region slight prominent (
<figureCitation box="[788,888,252,277]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1923,1945]" captionTargetBox="[159,1422,795,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[159,1423,795,1903]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 21. Amphidraus shenlong sp. nov. A–B male (A dorsal, B ventral); C–F left male palp (C ventral; D retroventral; E bulb, ventral; F femur + patella + tibia, retrolateral). Abbreviations: cc, cymbial conductor; dPED, distal process on embolic disc; e, embolus shaft; ef, embolic filament; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apophysis; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc. White arrow in D shows branchy projection of embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601388/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Fig. 21F</figureCitation>
); cymbium oval; cymbial conductor leaf-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[159,263,285,310]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1670,1692]" captionTargetBox="[177,1383,890,1615]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[151,1436,879,1648]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 22. Amphidraus shenlong sp. nov., left male palp (A ventral; B retrolateral). Abbreviations: cc, cymbial conductor; dPED, distal processes on embolic disc; e, embolus shaft; ed, embolic disc; ef, embolic filament; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apophysis; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601390/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Fig. 22A</figureCitation>
); tegulum with narrow lobe curved to retrolateral side (
<figureCitation box="[876,980,285,310]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1923,1945]" captionTargetBox="[159,1422,795,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[159,1423,795,1903]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 21. Amphidraus shenlong sp. nov. A–B male (A dorsal, B ventral); C–F left male palp (C ventral; D retroventral; E bulb, ventral; F femur + patella + tibia, retrolateral). Abbreviations: cc, cymbial conductor; dPED, distal process on embolic disc; e, embolus shaft; ef, embolic filament; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apophysis; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc. White arrow in D shows branchy projection of embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601388/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Figs 21E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[991,1043,286,310]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1670,1692]" captionTargetBox="[177,1383,890,1615]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[151,1436,879,1648]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 22. Amphidraus shenlong sp. nov., left male palp (A ventral; B retrolateral). Abbreviations: cc, cymbial conductor; dPED, distal processes on embolic disc; e, embolus shaft; ed, embolic disc; ef, embolic filament; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apophysis; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601390/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">22A</figureCitation>
); embolic disc with three processes very closer together: two rounded distal processes (dPED) almost fused and one short triangular ventral process (vPED) (
<figureCitation box="[251,356,351,376]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1923,1945]" captionTargetBox="[159,1422,795,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[159,1423,795,1903]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 21. Amphidraus shenlong sp. nov. A–B male (A dorsal, B ventral); C–F left male palp (C ventral; D retroventral; E bulb, ventral; F femur + patella + tibia, retrolateral). Abbreviations: cc, cymbial conductor; dPED, distal process on embolic disc; e, embolus shaft; ef, embolic filament; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apophysis; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc. White arrow in D shows branchy projection of embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601388/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Figs 21E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[368,420,352,376]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1670,1692]" captionTargetBox="[177,1383,890,1615]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[151,1436,879,1648]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 22. Amphidraus shenlong sp. nov., left male palp (A ventral; B retrolateral). Abbreviations: cc, cymbial conductor; dPED, distal processes on embolic disc; e, embolus shaft; ed, embolic disc; ef, embolic filament; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apophysis; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601390/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">22A</figureCitation>
). Embolic filament about as long as embolus shaft (
<figureCitation box="[1002,1169,351,376]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1923,1945]" captionTargetBox="[159,1422,795,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[159,1423,795,1903]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 21. Amphidraus shenlong sp. nov. A–B male (A dorsal, B ventral); C–F left male palp (C ventral; D retroventral; E bulb, ventral; F femur + patella + tibia, retrolateral). Abbreviations: cc, cymbial conductor; dPED, distal process on embolic disc; e, embolus shaft; ef, embolic filament; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apophysis; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc. White arrow in D shows branchy projection of embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601388/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Figs 21C, 21E</figureCitation>
). Color in alcohol (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1923,1945]" captionTargetBox="[159,1422,795,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[159,1423,795,1903]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 21. Amphidraus shenlong sp. nov. A–B male (A dorsal, B ventral); C–F left male palp (C ventral; D retroventral; E bulb, ventral; F femur + patella + tibia, retrolateral). Abbreviations: cc, cymbial conductor; dPED, distal process on embolic disc; e, embolus shaft; ef, embolic filament; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apophysis; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc. White arrow in D shows branchy projection of embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601388/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Figs 21</figureCitation>
A–B): cephalic area black; thoracic area yellow; abdomen dorsally variegated with yellow and brown; ventrally yellow; legs yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,151,576]" box="[206,425,452,477]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[206,300,452,477]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="472" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,151,576]" box="[206,1113,485,510]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[206,359,485,510]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[615,663,486,510]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">type</typeStatus>
locality (state of 
<collectingRegion box="[859,912,486,510]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Pará</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[923,993,485,510]" name="Brazil" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Brazil</collectingCountry>
) (
<figureCitation box="[1016,1100,485,510]" captionStart="FIGURE 30" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1729,1751]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,929,1708]" captionTargetId="figure@29.[151,1436,929,1708]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 30. Map of northern Brazil showing records of Amphidraus draconicaudatus, A. shenlong sp. nov. and A. draconitupan sp. nov. White lines represent the borders of Brazilian states. Acronyms of states: MG, Minas Gerais; MS, Mato Grosso do Sul; PA, Pará; SP, São Paulo; TO, Tocantins. Map modified from Google Earth ®." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2601406/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
